main event: Two observers watched an egg-shaped fiery object pass overhead in Yorktown-Walden, New York on 5 Feb 67.
interesting points: Both observers described the object as egg-shaped with exhaust or flame coming from the rear., The object was traveling at a high rate of speed and lasted for 30 seconds., Witnesses stated that the object shook their house as it passed over., The observed object was likely the afterburner of an F-101 aircraft making a low pass nearby., The object was described as having a fiery tail and making a thunderous noise.
